first, flash an open kernel {see flashing/instructions}

ON N9:
1) enable dev mode to get a terminal:
Settings -> Security {???} -> Dev Mode
phone will restart after it is done installing
you can just wait {about 2 minutes} once it prompts for:
  ~2.6MB additional installation required

2) open a terminal
devel-su #password is rootme
passwd user #any password

3) insert usb, select: sync and connect

ON PC:
ssh-keygen -f ~/.ssh/known_hosts -R 192.168.2.15
ssh-keygen -f ~/.ssh/known_hosts -R `cat .hostname`
sudo ifconfig usb0 192.168.2.14 netmask 255.255.255.0 up
scp ssh-config user@192.168.2.15:/tmp
ssh user@192.168.2.15

devel-su #rootme
sh /tmp/ssh-config #should prompt you for password twice and throw you off

#you can now ssh as root

0) dev mode + ssh-config
1) set-host
2) keygen.pl
3) install-sane
4) config-files
5) install-packages
